sub_topic: Prove that the empty set is a subset of every set.
message_1: Let A be a set such that A = {2, 4, 6}. Determine whether the empty set is a subset of A or not.
message_2: The empty set, denoted as âˆ… or {}, is a subset of every set, including set A. This is because there are no elements in the empty set that are not in set A (or any other set). So, the empty set is a subset of A.
